		Configuration Requirements

- UCR CS Server with Linux

-------------------------------------------------------

		Compiling Instructions

A makefile is provided with the source code.

Commands: make, make clean

- To compile: type 'make'
- To clean all unnecessary files: type 'make clean'

You may also use g++.

- To compile with g++: type 'g++ observer.cpp'

-------------------------------------------------------

		Operating Instructions

- type ' a.out "period" "interval" ' without the quotes

where "period" and "interval" are integers values.

-------------------------------------------------------

		Program Objective

- To print out the kernel's states for given interval 
  and period